 MRS Christiana Ekanem, an official of University of Calabar Teaching Hospital who was kidnapped in her home in Calabar, the state capital, on March 10, has been freed. Mr Ani Esin, State Security Adviser, Southern Senatorial District to Governor Ben Ayade, confirmed her release in a telephone interview with News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) yesterday in Calabar. Esin told NAN that Ekanem was released on Saturday night in Calabar, after being in captivity for 11 days. “As we speak, Mrs Ekanem was released on Saturday night here in Calabar. She has been re-united with her family. She was released safe and unhurt. The intervention was the collaborative efforts of security agencies in the state and my office,” he said.